Question: One image shows one primarily yellow train headed leftward, and the other image shows on primarily red train headed rightward.

Reference Answer: False

Left image URL: https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/originals/6c/5c/e0/6c5ce08e3a64e19812da15eb2ef141fc.jpg

Right image URL: https://c2.staticflickr.com/4/3041/2681570540_0d67ae769d_z.jpg?zz=1

Original program:

```
ANSWER0=VQA(image=LEFT,question='Is the train primarily yellow?')
ANSWER1=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='Is the train primarily red?')
ANSWER2=VQA(image=LEFT,question='Is the train headed leftward?')
ANSWER3=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='Is the train headed rightward?')
ANSWER4=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER0} and {ANSWER2}')
ANSWER5=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER1} and {ANSWER3}')
ANSWER6=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER4} xor {ANSWER5}')
FINAL_ANSWER=RESULT(var=ANSWER6)
```
